comment: Randolph (MEM) makes contact with Sullinger (BOS) that affects his RSBQ.
Gasol (MEM) steps into the lane causing Johnson (BOS) to react and step into the lane prior to the FT attempt by Sullinger (BOS). The officials stop the FT attempt and reset all players.
Sullinger (BOS) obtains a legal guarding position and jumps vertically as he absorbs the contact while contesting Green's (MEM) layup attempt.
Crowder (BOS) legally contests Green's (MEM) putback dunk attempt.
RHH shows that Crowder (BOS) makes contact with Randolph's (MEM) arm that affects his layup attempt.
Allen (MEM) makes incidental contact with Bradley (BOS) that does not affect his RSBQ.
Bradley (BOS) dribbles the ball high, but his hand remains on the top part of the ball.
Gasol (MEM) makes contact with Bradley's (BOS) arm that affects his layup attempt.
Allen (MEM) maintains a legal guarding position on the driving layup attempt by Smart (BOS).
Smart (BOS) grabs Chalmer's (MEM) arm affecting his RSBQ.
Crowder (BOS) commits a take foul on Allen (MEM).
L-SLA shows that Gasol (MEM) releases his dribble prior to moving his pivot foot (left foot).
Johnson (BOS) commits a take foul on Barnes (MEM).
Chalmers (MEM) makes contact with Thomas (BOS) on the layup attempt that causes the ball to become loose.
Crowder (BOS) grabs and holds Randolph's (MEM) arm affecting his ability to get open during the inbounds play.
Bradley (BOS) commits a take foul on Chalmers (MEM).
Sullinger (BOS) sets the screen on Allen (MEM) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
Gasol (MEM) makes contact with Thomas' (BOS) arm that affects his layup attempt.
RATR shows that Thomas (BOS) makes incidental contact with Barnes (MEM) while defending the inbounds play.
Barnes (MEM) and Green (MEM) legally contest Bradley's (BOS) jump shot attempt.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court that Thomas' (BOS) released the shot after the clock had expired was confirmed.
